    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on a high-ceiling matchup today, spearheaded by **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our premier efficiency score of 81.88. **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and a favorable matchup against McCullers Jr., whose xERA of 4.94 suggests a prime opportunity to drive up our counting stats. Crucially, the slow delivery from the opposing mound provides a green light for **Gunnar Henderson** to hunt stolen bases, a vital component of our strategy given the scarcity of the category. **Jacob Wilson** also draws a highly favorable start in the leadoff spot; his 71.63 score is elevated by an aggressive 10% park factor and the platoon advantage against the left-handed Cameron, making him a high-floor asset in our quest for runs and stolen bases.\n\nWe are navigating a few marginal start decisions, most notably with **Nasim Nunez**, who holds a 45.92 efficiency score. While **Nasim Nunez** sits at the lower end of our active spectrum, we are leaning into his elite sprint speed against Peralta; the 92% SB probability against this specific pitcher makes him a strategic hold in the MI slot despite his lower raw output. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, on the other hand, provides a more stable floor at 59.83, buoyed by a strong platoon edge against right-handed pitching that outweighs his park-adjusted headwinds. While **Drake Baldwin** and **Heliot Ramos** remain in the mid-50s, their spots in the top-two of their respective lineups ensure enough plate appearances to keep them as viable daily staples.\n\nRegarding the bench, our decision-making remains hampered by a wave of inactivity. With **Kyle Tucker**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Andy Pages** all facing an off-day, our depth is significantly constrained. **Luis Robert Jr.** remains on the IL, leaving no immediate pinch-hit threats to rotate into the starting nine. We continue to monitor the status of **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Josh Lowe** for future rotations, alongside high-upside developmental assets like **Coby Mayo**, **Brady House**, and **Miguel Vargas**. For today, we are effectively locked into this configuration, prioritizing speed and order position to mitigate the lack of bench flexibility. Keep a close eye on the weather and late lineup scratches, as any shift in the batting order for **Drake Baldwin** or **Heliot Ramos** could necessitate a recalibration of our efficiency targets.",
